pan class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/w/index.php?title=3DBayes%27_theorem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D=
5" title=3D"Edit section: For continuous random variables"><span>edit</span=
></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>For two continuous <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Random_varia=
ble" title=3D"Random variable">random variables</a> <i>X</i> and <i>Y</i>, =
Bayes' theorem may be analogously derived from the definition of <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conditional_density" class=3D"mw-redirect" t=
itle=3D"Conditional density">conditional density</a>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e f_{X\vert Y=3Dy}(x)=3D{\frac {f_{X,Y}(x,y)}{f_{Y}(y)}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
