 theorem">Radon=E2=80=93Nikodym theorem</a>. This was formulated by <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrey_Kolmogorov" title=3D"Andrey Kolmog=
orov">Kolmogorov</a> in 1933. Kolmogorov underlines the importance of condi=
tional probability, writing, "I wish to call attention to ... the theory of=
 conditional probabilities and conditional expectations".<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayes%27=
_theorem#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Bayes' theorem determines the posterio=
r distribution from the prior distribution. Uniqueness requires continuity =
assumptions.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayes%27_theorem#cite_note-19"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Bayes' the=
orem can be generalized to include improper prior distributions such as the=
 uniform distribution on the real line.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayes%27_theorem#cite_note=
-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> Modern <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markov_cha=
in_Monte_Carlo" title=3D"Markov chain Monte Carlo">Markov chain Monte Carlo=
</a> methods have boosted the importance of Bayes' theorem, including in ca=
ses with improper priors.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-21" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayes%27_theorem#cite_note-21"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p>
</p>
