<li>50 of them are users and 45 of them give true positive (0.90 =C3=97 50)=
</li></ul>
<p>The 1,000 people thus have 235 positive tests, of which only 45 are genu=
ine, about 19%.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Sensitivity_or_specificity"=
>Sensitivity or specificity</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/i=
ndex.php?title=3DBayes%27_theorem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=
=3D"Edit section: Sensitivity or specificity"><span>edit</span></a><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The importance of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Specificity_(=
tests)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Specificity (tests)">specificity</a>=
 can be seen by showing that even if sensitivity is raised to 100% and spec=
ificity remains at 80%, the probability that someone who tests positive is =
a cannabis user rises only from 19% to 21%, but if the sensitivity is held =
at 90% and the specificity is increased to 95%, the probability rises to 49=
%.
</p>
