<p>Hence, 2.4% of the total output is defective.
</p><p>We are given that <i>Y</i> has occurred and we want to calculate the=
 conditional probability of <i>X</i><sub>C</sub>. By Bayes' theorem,
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e P(X_{C}|Y)=3D{\frac {P(Y|X_{C})P(X_{C})}{P(Y)}}=3D{\frac {0.01\cdot 0.50}=
{0.024}}=3D{\frac {5}{24}}}">
