|B)\propto P(A)\cdot P(B|A).}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>In words, the posterior is proportional to the prior times the likelihoo=
d. This version of Bayes' theorem is known as Bayes' rule.<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-25" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayes%2=
7_theorem#cite_note-25"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template" =
style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Wikipedia:Citing_sources" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citing sources"><span title=3D=
"This citation requires a reference to the specific page or range of pages =
in which the material appears. (August 2025)">page&nbsp;needed</span></a></=
i>]</sup>
</p><p>If events <i>A</i><sub>1</sub>, <i>A</i><sub>2</sub>, ..., are mutua=
lly exclusive and exhaustive, i.e., one of them is certain to occur but no =
two can occur together, we can determine the proportionality constant by us=
ing the fact that their probabilities must add up to one.<sup class=3D"nopr=
int Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wiki=
pedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliab=
le sources. (August 2025)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> For instan=
ce, for a given event <i>A</i>, the event <i>A</i> itself and its complemen=
t =C2=AC<i>A</i> are exclusive and exhaustive. Denoting the constant of pro=
portionality by <i>c</i>, we have:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e P(A|B)=3Dc\cdot P(A)\cdot P(B|A){\text{ and }}P(\neg A|B)=3Dc\cdot P(\neg=
 A)\cdot P(B|\neg A).}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">|</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>c</mi>
        <mo>=E2=8B=85<!-- =E2=8B=85 --></mo>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=E2=8B=85<!-- =E2=8B=85 --></mo>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
