)=3D\sum _{j}P(B\cap A_{j}),}"></span>
</p><p>Or (using the multiplication rule for conditional probability),<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-27" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Bayes%27_theorem#cite_note-27"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>26=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
