A\cap B\cap C)=3DP(B\cap A\cap C)=3DP(B\vert A\cap C)\,P(A\vert C)\,P(C)}">=
</span></dd></dl>
<p>The desired result is obtained by identifying both expressions and solvi=
ng for <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 P(A\vert B\cap C)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo fence=3D"false" stretchy=3D"false">|</mo>
